HEADWORD: Flagellant
<hw>Flag"el*lant</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>flagellans</ets>, p. p. of <ets>flagellare</ets>: cf.F.
<ets>flagellant</ets>. See <er>Flagellate</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Eccl.
Hist.)</fld> <def>One of a fanatical sect which flourished in Europe in
the 13th and 14th centuries, and maintained that flagellation was of
equal virtue with baptism and the sacrament; -- called also
<altname>disciplinant</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Flagellata</ent>⟦br⟧
